{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsYceJpDYKEU3YwsJovJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All checks pass, no restrictive `cluster.routing.allocation.enable` setting present.\n\n## Root cause & fix\n\nThe `es-config` ConfigMap (mounted via `subPath`, so updates don't auto-propagate to running pods) had two bugs:\n1. `node.name:` was set with an empty value instead of `${POD_NAME}` — ES 7.17.9 refuses to start on a null-valued setting.\n2. `discovery.seed_hosts` pointed at `*.es-cluster.default.svc.cluster.local` instead of the actual `elasticsearch` namespace.\n\n`es-cluster-0` and `es-cluster-1` were already running with a valid in-memory config from before the ConfigMap was corrupted, so they stayed healthy as a 2-node cluster. When `es-cluster-2` restarted, it picked up the broken config file and crash-looped (`RunContainerError`).\n\n**Fix applied:**\n- Corrected the ConfigMap (`node.name: ${POD_NAME}`, seed hosts fixed to the `elasticsearch` namespace).\n- Deleted the `es-cluster-2` pod to force a fresh mount of the corrected config (required since `subPath` mounts don't live-update).\n\n**Verification:**\n- Cluster health: `green`, 3/3 nodes.\n- `/_cat/nodes` shows all three: `es-cluster-0`, `es-cluster-1`, `es-cluster-2`.\n- `app-data` index search returns its document successfully.\n- No restrictive `cluster.routing.allocation.enable` setting was present.\n\nNo operators/CRDs were installed; only the existing ConfigMap and pod were touched."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":493,"cache_read_input_tokens":101218,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":493},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"52ec2a3c-713e-41c5-84eb-a38d7e2aece9","uuid":"1921e9d5